16 (2) 'Peer-to-peer payment platform' means an online digital platform that allows a user
17 to transfer funds from his or her bank account to another person's bank account.
18 (b) Any money transmitter that operates a peer-to-peer payment platform shall delay the
19 processing of any transaction on such platform involving the transfer of funds initiated by
20 a user of such platform for a period of not less than 15 minutes, during which time such
21 user shall be able to cancel the transaction.
22 (c) Any money transmitter that violates this Code section shall be subject to the penalties
23 provided in this part."
24 SECTION 2.
25 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
